# Documentation site — environment configuration
#
# This example is fully static: public pages, no auth, no AI, no email. It runs
# with zero configuration. Copy to `.env` only if you want to override a default.

# --- Database (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# A docs site has no tables, so the database is never touched. Left here only
# for parity with the other examples. Unset = zero-config SQLite (the default).
# DATABASE_URL=postgres://user:pass@localhost:5432/docs

# --- Content ---------------------------------------------------------------
# The docs are plain `.md` files under `content/docs/`. Resolved relative to the
# directory you run `sovrium start` from, so run it from the project root.
# There is nothing to configure here — add a file, get a route.
